HEADWORD: Graystone
<hw>Gray"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A grayish or greenish compact rock, composed of feldspar and
augite, and allied to basalt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

